  "text": "We generate our training and test pairs as reported in [CITATION_1] . The pairs can be of two kinds: similar pairs, obtained pairing together two binary functions originated by the same source code, and dissimilar pairs, obtained pairing randomly functions that do not derive from the same source code. Specifically, for each function in our datasets we create two pairs, a similar pair, associated with training label +1 and a dissimilar pair, training label −1; obtaining a total number of pairs that is twice the total number of functions.",
